{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "DigitalPlants",
  "description": "DigitalPlants — 400×400 grid of cubes lifted onto a morphing cylinder ↔ torus surface, with simplex-noise stem displacement, FBM petal fracturing, per-instance hash rotation, neighbour smoothing, and cel-shaded cube rendering with PCF shadows. First decomposition of the topology-wrap generator family: the graph wires node.grid_uv_field → per-instance noise/math → cyl + tor wrap fields → blend_copies → rotation jitter → neighbor_smooth → digital_plants_render. Every legacy compute-shader step is reproduced as a curated primitive — node.simplex_noise_per_copy, node.fractal_noise_per_copy, node.array_math (with ShapePowClip / MirrorRamp / ScaleOffset ops), node.cylinder_wrap_field, node.torus_wrap_field, node.position_jitter, node.rotation_jitter, node.blend_copies — so the same vocabulary can be reused by future generators (stem fields, ring fields, plant variants).\n\nThe `morph` slider continuously interpolates between cylinder-stem and torus-flower topologies via node.blend_copies (NOT node.switch_array — selection vs interpolation matters here). `base_radius` is multiplied by (1 - morph) for the cylinder branch so it shrinks toward zero in flower mode, matching legacy. `instance_scale` follows `box_scale * (1 + morph * 3)` so cube size grows with petal density.\n\nCamera params are exposed in DEGREES on the outer card (cam_orbit / cam_tilt / cam_fov) and converted to RADIANS by three node.scale_offset_value nodes before reaching node.digital_plants_render. The cam_orbit_rad node adds π/2 to compensate for the orbit convention difference between the legacy compute and the new render primitive (legacy looks down +Z at orbit=0; render primitive looks down +X — adding π/2 rotates back to legacy's view).",
  "presetMetadata": {
    "id": "DigitalPlants",
    "displayName": "Digital Plants",
    "category": "Geometry",
    "oscPrefix": "digitalPlants",
    "available": true,
    "params": [
